their son. He shakes my hand limply and avoids my gaze. He sits
down, and for two minutes there is silence. I'm giving him time to
see if he'll shape the interview at all. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. I hear there have been some troubles. I guess you're here to
see whether I can be of some help.
</P>
<P>
   A. Yup.
</P>
<P>
   Q. You probably don't want to talk to me. Why would you? You
don't know if you can trust me, and it sounds like you haven't been
talking much anyway lately, but I'll make a suggestion.
</P>
<P>
   A. What?
</P>
<P>
   Q. I think it might be useful to you to talk to me. I have a
sense that people have been on your case, and at least I'd be
someone who could listen to what is going on, because things don't
sound so hot right now.
</P>
<P>
   A. (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)(Whispered)(END ITALICS HERE) OK
</P>
<P>
   Q. So what really brought you here?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, my parents are getting worried about me because I'm
getting into fights all the time.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)He's not denying problems, but describes
them through someone else's eyes. This tells me he's not ready to
take responsibility, or he's frightened to say something is wrong.
But he's not out of touch with reality, and not uncooperative.(END
ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. So what's making you upset and angry?
</P>
<P>
   A. You know, I have to say it's kind of weird.
</P>
<P>
   Q. What's weird?
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)(He's quiet again.) (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. Who are you angry at?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, that's it. I'm just angry at everybody.
</P>
<P>
   Q. How long has this been going on?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, maybe a month or so.
</P>
<P>
   Q. What's been happening?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, I get into fights with a lot of guys and my Mom is on
my back a lot. Nag nag nag.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Anything else?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, yeah. Then there's my history teacher. Yesterday she
just went at me.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Went at you?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, she wouldn't leave me alone. I didn't know the answer,
and she just kept asking me.
</P>
<P>
   Q. And what did you do?
</P>
<P>
   A. I just started screaming at her: ``Get the hell away from me!
Leave me alone!'' And she sent me to the principal and they called
my parents.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Anything like that ever happen before to you?
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) I am trying to get at whether there is a
history of angry outbursts. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   A. No, nothing like this, although I have been feeling I guess
not so good for the last two months.
</P>
<P>
   Q. So when your teacher did that it must have been really
upsetting to you, must have really hurt you.
</P>
<P>
   A. Why do you think that?
</P>
<P>
   Q. Well, you yelled at her. You felt out of control, and if I
were in that class and if it were me, I'd feel really ashamed about
the whole thing.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) I'm putting myself in his shoes, and
letting him know he's not crazy. The reason he can't talk is he's
afraid of what will happen to him. Like many boys in trouble, he
needs desperately to hide his shame that he's falling apart inside.
(END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   A. I guess I should have left her alone, but I just couldn't
stand it. And I just had these ideas. Well, I don't know, never
mind. They're not important.
</P>
<P>
   Q. I think this is one of those things you probably don't want
to talk to somebody you don't know about.
</P>
<P>
   A. Yup.
</P>
<P>
   Q. I can't promise anything, but look how upset you were. Maybe
if you try to talk to me I could at least try to get people off
your back.
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, I just had this idea that I'd like to get up and sock
her right in the mouth. (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)(Adding quickly)(END
ITALICS HERE) But I'd never do it.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) We now know he has some potential for
violence, and he's on the edge. That doesn't mean he's going to do
it, but there's the potential. His aggression is the surface
expression of what is, in many boys, an underlying depression. I
have interviewed hundreds of boys like this.(END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. What do your friends say about all of this?
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)I'm trying to assess, does he still have
friends, is he connected to people, is he telling anybody else and
what are his peers saying. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   A. I don't see them much anymore.
</P>
<P>
   Q. What do you do?
</P>
<P>
   A. Mostly watch TV by myself.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) He's loosening up. Now I ask about his
plans, thoughts and fantasies _ not just his actions.(END ITALICS
HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. And do you think about anything while you're watching TV?
</P>
<P>
   A. It's just a weird idea that goes through my mind. I told you
with these things, I'd never do them.
</P>
<P>
   Q. I know these are just your thoughts, but I think it would
really help to hear them.
</P>
<P>
   A. You sure you won't think I'm crazy?
</P>
<P>
   Q. Let's hear them.
</P>
<P>
   A. My friend's father, next door, has this collection of guns. I
think they use them to start races.
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
<P>
   Q. And so what did you think about those?
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, I've never really stolen anything, I wouldn't want to.
It's just kind of an image I have.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Kind of like a dream, huh?
</P>
<P>
   A. Yeah.
</P>
<P>
   Q. And what happens in that dream?
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) If he can talk about his fantasies as
dreams, at some distance, maybe he won't be so frightened and will
open up. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, that's why it's so weird and upsetting. I've got one of
those guns in my hand.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) I'm starting to feel a little nervous. He's
on edge enough to potentially do something, not that I think he's
going to. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   A. And my mom is lying on the floor.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)(He is quiet and looks scared.)(END ITALICS
HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. It's scary to talk about all of this.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)(He nods.) (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. I think that's because there's even more, isn't there? My
guess is the rest of it isn't just about other people.
</P>
<P>
   A. How the hell would you know something like that?
</P>
<P>
   Q. I don't really know it, but I've helped other guys who've had
these kinds of dreams and ideas before.
</P>
<P>
   A. Well, I guess I've got to say you're right. I think about
maybe shooting me.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Have you ever thought about hurting yourself before?
</P>
<P>
   A. Just a couple of times.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Have you ever had a plan?
</P>
<P>
   A. Yeah, the gun was one plan, and then I saw a show once on TV
where someone used rope and they hung themselves. I've thought
about that once or twice.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) I want to know how far he's taken his
plans. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. Did you actually buy the rope or get the gun?
</P>
<P>
   A. No, I'd never really hurt anybody, I told you.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)(He starts to tear up.) (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   Q. That might be true, but I'm concerned that you're very close
to hurting yourself, and then who knows what else could happen.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) I'm emphasizing my empathy for him, not
just protecting others. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   A. The only thing I don't get is, sometimes I feel down, but
sometimes I have a lot of energy.
</P>
<P>
   Q. I think that's actually part of the problem. You're up and
down. And when you have the energy I think even YOU know you're
afraid of what you might do.
</P>
<P>
   A. What happens now?
</P>
<P>
   Q. I think it would be important we both do something. We both
know you need help and you need it right away. I know you won't
like this suggestion, but I think it would be good at least for a
short time to use the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   He was hospitalized for about two weeks and treated with
medication and psychotherapy. As he got a little less depressed and
more trusting it came out that he had witnessed his biological
father abusing his mother, starting when he was about 5 years old.
He is now in his early 20s. He has intermittent therapy for
depression. His fantasies of violence sometimes return, but he has
never been violent to date toward anyone. (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
