   COXNET INSIDE NASCAR 0414: SHOCK DEBATE _ At Daytona, NASCAR
controlled the rear and front shocks put on every Winston Cup car.
At Talladega, the sports governing body has said it will only be in
charge of the rear shocks, leaving the front up to the team. What
do drivers think about all of this? Do they think this will cause
the cars to perform better or worse than Daytona? What difference
will it make to be able to put in your own front shocks? NASCAR
already controls the restrictor plates at Talladega, how do drivers
