u s BC-SWM-HALLOFFAME16-COX     04-15 0390
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SWM-HALLOFFAME16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hall of Fame pays tribute to swimmers
 &HT;    who were poetry in motion
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. _ The Summer Olympics are several months
and half a world away.
</P>
<P>
   Why wait for televised excitement in Sydney when you can visit
the International Swimming Hall of Fame right now?
</P>
<P>
   The Hall of Fame complex has two Olympic-size pools and several
diving boards that are open to the public daily during certain
hours.
</P>
<P>
   And the pools are fast _ eight world records have been set at
the complex, two in one day in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   Indoors, the Hall of Fame has aquatic memorabilia galore. An
original Olympic flag. The starting block that Mark Spitz used in
Munich. Swimsuits and warm-up jackets of former swimming stars.
</P>
<P>
   Best of all, it's home to three former Olympians _ in wax, that
is.
</P>
<P>
   DUKE KAHANAMOKU
</P>
<P>
   Because the Hawaiian won Olympic medals in 1912, 1920, 1924 and
1932. Because he helped introduce the rest of the world to surfing.
Because he descended from Hawaiian royalty, but was known for his
humble nature and easy charm. Because he appeared in 30 Hollywood
movies, served as sheriff of Honolulu for 26 years, and in between
worked for two years as a gas station operator. Because, when asked
who taught him the crawl, he said, ``No one.''
</P>
<P>
   JOHNNY WEISSMULLER
</P>
<P>
   Because he went from spindly boy to strapping young man after
taking up swimming. Because he won five gold medals at the 1924 and
'28 Olympics, and broke the world record in the
</P>
<P>
   100-yard freestyle five times in five years. Because he cut a
fine figure in a loincloth and simply was Tarzan to Jane, Boy,
Cheetah and generations of moviegoers. Because after 12 Tarzan
films, he became Jungle Jim for 16 more movies.
</P>
<P>
   MARK SPITZ
</P>
<P>
   Because he's the original Olympic golden child, winner of seven
gold medals in seven events at the '72 Games (to add to his two
golds, silver and bronze from Mexico City four years earlier).
Because his wax replica proudly wears his Olympic parade uniform,
which is so quintessentially early '70s. Because he attempted a
comeback, at the age of 40, by trying out for the 1992 Olympic
team. Because we love his 'stache as much as his smile.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-15-00 1412EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
