<HEADLINE>
THIS IS ONE FOR THE BOOKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT -- The previous record for the fastest six goals to
start a playoff game also involved the Red Wings back on April 7,
1988 again st Toronto. The teams did it in 10:22 of play, more than
three minutes longer than it took the Kings and Wings to do it
(6:56) Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Detroit won that game, too, 6-2, against Maple Leafs goaltender
Ken Wregget, who now is the Red Wings backup.
</P>
<P>
   It was far different from Game 1 Thursday night when the Red
Wings' 2-0 victory included an empty net goal by Sergei Fedorov.
</P>
<P>
   ``Teams often feel each other out in the first game of a
series,'' Detroit coach Scotty Bowman said. ``But there can be
surprises too. I remember a playoff series between Montreal and
Chicago that had Ken Dryden and Tony Esposito. You can't do any
better than that, but the game ended 9-7.''
</P>
<P>
   /
</P>
<P>
   The Kings and Wings combined for seven goals in the first period
Saturday. The last time two teams did that in a playoff period was
May 20, 1997 in the Eastern Conference between Philadelphia and the
New York Rangers. The Flyers won the period 4-3 and the game 6-3.
</P>
<P>
   No stopping Lapointe: Saturday marked the first playoff
three-goal game of Martin Lapointe's six-year NHL career. He had
his first regular-season hat trick just two weeks ago against the
New York Rangers.
</P>
<P>
   Kings coach Andy Murray said after Thursday's low scoring Game 1
that the scrappy Lapointe might have been the best Red Wing on the
ice. Saturday, that diligence resulted in goals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just try to get open and work hard in the corners,''
Lapointe said. ``I make sure every time I get a chance, I bear down
and make sure to get a shot on net.''
</P>
<P>
   Berg for Game 3? Kings defenseman Aki Berg is not playing and
he's not very happy. But at age 23, he knows his time will come,
maybe Monday night when the series moves to Los Angeles. Rookie
Jere Ka ralahti had a difficult first period Saturday and played
sparingly after whiffing on a puck that Lapointe turned into the
Wings' second goal.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is tough to watch, no question, but that is a coach's
decision,'' Berg said. ``I have nothing to say about (Saturday's)
game. I am just staying ready for my turn.''
</P>
<P>
   Quick Whistles: The last time teams scored 13 goals in a game,
it actually was 15, April 29, 1993 when the Kings beat Calgary 9-6.
The record is 18, set April 7, 1982 when the Kings beat Edmonton 1
0-8. Two games later the Kings won the Miracle on Manchester and
went on to win the series in five games. .... Saturday, the two
teams had six g oals after 19 shots. Thursday, they had none after
16. ... The Kings imm ediately flew back to Los Angeles and will
practice this afternoon at th eir training facility in El Segundo.
</P>
</TEXT>
